# Copy this file to client/.env and adjust as needed. Restart the Vite dev server
# after changes. There is no dev proxy — the client always calls the Go servers
# directly with absolute URLs (defaults live in @files-workbench/core, src/api-config.js).
#
# Using 127.0.0.1 instead of localhost keeps API calls on a separate browser
# HTTP connection pool from media requests (thumbnails, previews), which prevents
# thumbnail loading from blocking directory listing requests.
#
# If large responses (previews, plugin artifacts, media) hang while small JSON
# requests work, your machine's IPv4 loopback may be dropping big TCP payloads —
# use IPv6 loopback instead:
#   VITE_API_BASE=http://[::1]:8001
#   VITE_CONTROL_BASE=http://[::1]:8002
VITE_API_BASE=http://127.0.0.1:8001
VITE_CONTROL_BASE=http://localhost:8002
